{"lemma":"بانِيَةٌ","slug":"بانِيَةٌ","root":"ب.ن.#","root_slug":"ب-ن-_","root_link":"/words/roots/ب-ن-_","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":0},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n3367"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A8%D8%A7%D9%86%D9%90%D9%8A%D9%8E%D8%A9%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":null,"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n3367","headword_ar":"بَانِيَةٌ","root":"bnY","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"fem. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baAnK","text_ar":"بَانٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]. ―         -b2-  Also sing. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bawaAnK","text_ar":"بَوَانٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) which signifies The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ribs of"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the breast,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the part thereof called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zawor","text_ar":"زَوْر"},{"kind":"text","text":": (M, K:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bones of the breast:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"shoulder-blades"},{"kind":"page_break","n":262},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and the four legs:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) and the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"legs"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a she-camel. (M, K.) One says, [likening a man to a camel lying down,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aloqaY bawaAniyhu","text_ar":"اَلْقَى بَوَانِيهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He took up his abode, and settled,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, M, K,) in a place; like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aloqaY EaSaAhu","text_ar":"اَلْقَى عَصَاهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (T, M.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aloqaY Al$~aA^omu bawaAniyahu","text_ar":"اَلْقَى الشَّاْمُ بَوَانِيَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Syria became in a settled state"},{"kind":"text","text":"] occurs in a trad. as related by A'Obeyd: and if he said"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bawaAy^inahu","text_ar":"بَوَايِنَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", it would be allowable;"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bawaAy^inu","text_ar":"بَوَايِنُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"being pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bwAn","text_ar":"بوان"},{"kind":"text","text":", [i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buwaAnN","text_ar":"بُوَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biwaAnN","text_ar":"بِوَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] which is a name for any tent-pole except in the middle of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bayot","text_ar":"بَيْت"},{"kind":"text","text":", which has three poles. (T.) And it is said in another trad.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aloqati Als~amaA='u biraka bawaAniyhaA","text_ar":"اَلْقَتِ السَّمَا=ءُ بِرَكَ بَوَانِيهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The sky cast down the rain that it contained."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"}],"source_refs":["TA","M","K","T"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}